/**
    @defgroup NMaxPerMeshOptions Specifying Per Mesh Options

    The <b>Nebula2 3DSMax Toolkit</b> provides per-mesh options which let you 
    handle the mesh to fit it for your own purpose.

    Be sure that the model which you want to apply the mesh option is selected 
    before you click the <i>Mesh Options</i> menu item on the Nebula2 menu. 

    @image html meshoption01.png "Mesh Option menu item on Nebula2 menu"

    If you want to remove 'mesh options' from the model which aleady has
    'mesh options', select the model then click <i>'Mesh Options'</i>
    menu item once again. It will remove the mesh options from the selected
    model.
    
    The applied mech options can be found on the modify panel.

    @image html meshoption02.png "Mesh Optio rollout on the modify panel"

      - <b>Mesh Types</b>
        - Normal - normal mesh type which is default option
        - Swing - indicate that the mesh is <tt>swing shapenode</tt>.
        - Shadow - indicate that the mesh is <tt>shadow</tt> model.
        - Collision - indicate that the mesh will be used for <tt>collison</tt> mesh. 
      - <b>Vertex Options</b>
        - Normal - the exported mesh will contains vertex normal.
        - Color - the exported mesh will contains vertex color.
        - Uvs - the exported mesh will constains uvs for its texturing.
        - Tangent - generate tangent per vertex for per pixel lighting

*/
